reviewText: Very enjoyable DVD documentary of the band's trip to Alaska.  This is a very talented and fun band.  This DVD gives a behind the scenes look at things beyond a concert.
Love the NGDB and this is one welcome addition to my library
Very good, I enjoy it and loved the scenic beauty of Alaska.
Wonderful video of a great band in Alaska. Intimate view and very cool.

ITS GREAT BUT I GAVE IT 4 STARS "WHAT??!!"  ITS ONLY 45 MINUTES LONG . IT SHOULD HAVE BEEN 2 HOURS LONG. IF IT WAS I WOULD GIVE IT 10 STARS. NEEDED ALOT MORE CONCERT FOOTAGE. LEAVES YOU THIRSTY FOR ALOT MORE.
Very enjoyable tour with NGDB, and makes me want to visit Alaska.
An excellent video shot in such beautiful locations (I'm determined to get there one day). "I Fought The Law" was such a delightful surpise; I felt as if I had received a gift.

A very good piece on the Dirt Band,doesn't hurt that they are cruising thru the 50th state either.
 A must for all Dirt Band Fanatics.
